sp.p:
You see Kinsman I am somewhat bold to  call in, and see 
			how you do, I heard you were safe enough, and I was very glad 
			of  it that  it was no  worse;

Come, let me tell you, you are too unkind a Kinsman in faith; 
			the Captain loving you so  dearly, aye, like  the Pomewater of his 
			eye, and you to  be so  uncomfortable, fie, fie.

Purgatory? tuh; that  word deserves to  be spit upon  ; 
			I wonder that  a man of sober tongue as you seem to  be, should 
			have the folly to  believe there is such a place.

aye, I knew by  their shuffling Clubs would be Trump; 
			Mass here is the Knave, if he can do any good upon   them: 
			Clubs, Clubs, Clubs.

Do you hear me, sir, I desire more acquaintance on  you, 
			you shall earn some money of me, now I know you can Conjure; 
			but can you fetch any that  is lost?
